      "writtenOn": "2026-05-21T15:06:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Will reword. The \"field pushdown\" terminology was for the old scheme that pushed _fields_ down into child arcs eagerly; the new scheme also keeps the \"pushdown\" name but pushes _dependencies_ (ArcPending placeholders) instead. Proposed reword for the opening paragraph: \"Switch the comprehension pushdown algorithm from field pushdown — eagerly materializing the body\u0027s fields on child arcs — to dependency pushdown: pre-create the arcs as ArcPending placeholders, run the comp eagerly when its guard fields are concrete, and let ArcPending propagate into the rest of the evaluator instead of materializing fields ahead of time.\" Will apply on the next amend (not amending here per the user\u0027s instructions).",
      "parentUuid": "f649c4b3_3f9b350d",
      "revId": "b0e804612cfe8c4e95cc5eae7c88b10d87c71e3a",
