      "writtenOn": "2026-05-21T15:06:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Will expand the explanation. The reason for the trim change: comprehensions used to appear as direct leaf conjuncts (`*adt.Comprehension`), so `trimv3.linkResolvers` matched them directly and walked their `Clauses` to install dependency links. With pushdown they no longer reach trim as leaf `*adt.Comprehension`s — they appear as `*Comprehension` decls inside a `*StructLit` leaf conjunct (the body wrapper). The patch detects this shape, walks the StructLit decls, and re-establishes the same per-clause links via `linkStructComprehension` so trim\u0027s reachability analysis is unchanged in outcome. Will add this paragraph to the commit message on next amend.",
      "parentUuid": "e0be100c_705c5232",
      "revId": "b0e804612cfe8c4e95cc5eae7c88b10d87c71e3a",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
