      "writtenOn": "2026-05-21T15:06:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Diagnosis: `updateArcType` is the silently no-op in this case. With `arc.ArcType \u003d\u003d ArcPending` (already checked above) and `t \u003d ArcNotPresent`, the function returns early at `if t \u003e\u003d v.ArcType` because ArcNotPresent\u0027s enum value (4) is greater than ArcPending\u0027s (3), i.e. ArcNotPresent is \"more restrictive\" per the enum order — so updateArcType refuses to widen back. The direct assignment was the actual change. Removed the no-op call and added a comment explaining why we have to bypass updateArcType here (no parent task is going to materialize this arc, so we force the transition). Edited in place.",
